<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1451,1963,2062]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,689]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="158" pageId="2" pageNumber="157">
Another name which is relevant for the nomenclature of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1818" box="[761,903,1963,1989]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="2" pageNumber="157" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[761,903,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="157">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName authority="J. de Vries" authorityName="J. de Vries" box="[934,1170,1963,1989]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="2" pageNumber="157" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[934,1056,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="157">R. vulgaris</emphasis>
J.de Vries
</taxonomicName>
bis (1779: 196). Matzke-Hajek (2016) argued that this name would be not validly published because it is not in a scientific publication and the text is only a translation of 
<bibRefCitation author="Valmont de Bomare, J. - C." box="[489,797,2035,2062]" pageId="2" pageNumber="157" refId="ref6693" refString="Valmont de Bomare, J. - C. (1765) Dictionnaire raisonne universel d'histoire naturelle 4. Brunet, Paris, 815 pp." type="book" year="1765">Valmont de Bomare (1765)</bibRefCitation>
which does not use binary nomenclature consistently and consequently is not validly published. However, De Vries presents his book as a scientific commentary on Martinet’s catechism, and moreover, though it is recommended to not publish in popular papers or books (
<emphasis box="[1182,1229,195,221]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">ICN</emphasis>
Art. 30A.4, 
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." pageId="3" pageNumber="158" refId="ref6527" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. [Regnum Vegetabile 159]. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[136,185,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), it is not forbidden, and a translation of an invalidly published text does not cause that also this translation is invalid if accepted by the author who uses it; many invalidly published texts serve as validating description by later authors. 
<taxonomicName box="[232,400,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[232,400,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Rubus vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is validly published as such. It is also clear that neither De Vries (who refers to Tournefort and to 
<bibRefCitation author="Duhamel de Monceau, M." box="[164,348,338,365]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" refId="ref5099" refString="Duhamel de Monceau, M. (1768) Traite des arbres fruitiers, contenant leur figure, leur sdescription, leur culture, etc. vol. 2. Saillant and Desaint, Paris, 280 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 16026" type="book" year="1768">Duhamel [1768]</bibRefCitation>
in his book) nor Valmont thought out the name 
<taxonomicName box="[879,1002,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[879,1002,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R. vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
themselves but adapted to common use, as many authors of that time refer to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bauh." authorityName="Bauh." box="[550,746,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[550,673,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R. vulgaris</emphasis>
Bauh.
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bauhin, C." box="[805,1010,374,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" refId="ref4820" refString="Bauhin, C. (1623) Pinax theatri botanici. Ludovici Regis, Basiliae, 518 pp." type="book" year="1623">Bauhin 1623: 479</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="158" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,158,689]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">
The type of 
<taxonomicName box="[337,464,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[337,464,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R. vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A." box="[697,978,410,437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" pagination="33 - 51" refId="ref6742" refString="Van de Beek, A. (2016) Validations of the Rubus taxa in Tournefort's Institutiones and their Corollarium in later literature. Adansonia 38 (1): 33 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / a 2016 n 1 a 4" type="journal article" year="2016">Van de Beek (2016: 36)</bibRefCitation>
and it is an illustration published in the Matthioli’s 
<emphasis box="[269,583,446,473]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Commentarii secundo aucti</emphasis>
(1559: 507). Though this picture is not very precise, it can, because of the strong prickles and rigid inflorescences, hardly be anything else than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schott" authorityYear="1818" box="[949,1096,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[949,1096,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the most common blackberry in 
<collectingCountry box="[167,218,518,544]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Italy</collectingCountry>
where Matthioli lived. However, the drawing does not give precise details so that it is not of a quality to identify it without knowing the broader context. Consequently, for a precise identification of this name an epitype is selected according to 
<emphasis box="[378,425,591,617]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">ICN</emphasis>
Art. 9.9 (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[572,789,590,617]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" refId="ref6527" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. [Regnum Vegetabile 159]. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 254 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[666,715,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). This material, a complete specimen, with leaves and welldeveloped flowers (
<figureCitation box="[359,425,626,652]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1858,1880]" captionTargetBox="[451,1137,602,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-200@2.[451,1137,602,1830]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Epitype of Rubus vulgaris J.de Vries bis (L, 2-D code L.1907626). Image courtesy of the herbarium L, reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5585398" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5585398/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), clearly represents the traditional concept (e.g., J. de Vries bis 1779: 196) and current use and application of 
<taxonomicName box="[345,468,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis box="[345,468,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R. vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Van de Beek 2016)" baseAuthorityName="Van de Beek" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[665,1042,662,689]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ulmifolius">
<emphasis box="[665,808,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="158">R. ulmifolius</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Van de Beek, A." box="[822,1034,662,689]" pageId="3" pageNumber="158" pagination="33 - 51" refId="ref6742" refString="Van de Beek, A. (2016) Validations of the Rubus taxa in Tournefort's Institutiones and their Corollarium in later literature. Adansonia 38 (1): 33 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / a 2016 n 1 a 4" type="journal article" year="2016">Van de Beek 2016</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
